SENATE RESOLUTION 7
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to recognize Teresa Newton on the occasion of
her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pause to
specially recognize those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and
enthusiasm throughout their careers in public service; and
WHEREAS, Teresa Newton is one such estimable individual, who, having rendered
many years of service as director of the Lawrence County Library, will take her much-deserved
retirement; and
WHEREAS, throughout the many blessed years of Ms. Newton's tenure, she has
consistently strived to be a facilitator of learning and love of literature for children and adults
alike; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Newton has been a witness to numerous library upgrades and helped
the institution to recover after a tornado; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Newton exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout her forty-eight-year career, Teresa Newton has demonstrated
the utmost professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration
of her colleagues and her community; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we extend to Teresa Newton
our heartfelt wishes for a happy and fulfilling retirement and every continued success in her
future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
